hat makes this plot have a log axis -->\n|yAxisMin = 1 <!-- Needed to avoid trying to show the values y2, y3 of 0, impossible on log scale because log(0)=-infinity -->\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n\n=== More plots ===\n[[File:COVID-19 in Singapore.svg|alt=\\|frameless|1000x1000px]]\n\n{{clear}}\n\n== Case details ==\nAs of 15 April 2020, there are a total of 3,699 confirmed cases with 652 discharged, as well as 10 confirmed deaths.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Clement |title=Record 447 new coronavirus cases in S'pore, of which 404 are linked to dormitories |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/record-447-new-coronavirus-cases-in-spore-of-which-404-are-linked-to-dormitories |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=15 April 2020 |date=15 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"15AprClu\">{{cite web |title=Record 447 new COVID-19 cases in Singapore, 68% linked to known clusters |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/covid-19-new-cases-record-447-cluster-local-unlinked-apr-15-12643698 |website=CNA |accessdate=15 April 2020 |date=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThroughout the outbreak, several clusters were discovered; namely the Life Church and Missions Singapore, Yong Thai Hang health products shop, a business meeting at Grand Hyatt hotel,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/novel-coronavirus-3-new-cases-confirmed-all-have-not-recently-travelled-china|title=3 Novel coronavirus: 3 new cases confirmed, all have not recently travelled to China|date=9 February 2020|website=TODAYonline|access-date=9 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210152715/https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/novel-coronavirus-3-new-cases-confirmed-all-have-not-recently-travelled-china|archive-date=10 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> the 10 Seletar Aerospace Heights construction site, the [[Grace Assembly of God]],<ref name=\"13FebMOH\">{{cite web |title=Eight More Confirmed Cases of COVID-19 Infection |work=MOH |url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/eight-more-confirmed-cases-of-covid-19-infection |accessdate=13 February 2020 |date=13 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213114302/https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/eight-more-confirmed-cases-of-covid-19-infection |archive-date=13 February 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Wizlearn Technologies (an e-learning firm at [[Singapore Science Park]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/new-coronavirus-cluster-at-e-learning-company-in-science-park-ii-with-4-staff|title=New coronavirus cluster at company in Science Park II with 4 staff infected, including 2 new cases announced|last1=Goh|first1=Timothy|last2=Kaur|first2=Karamjit|date=28 February 2020|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228123937/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/new-coronavirus-cluster-at-e-learning-company-in-science-park-ii-with-4-staff|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> a private singing event at [[SAFRA National Service Association|SAFRA]] Jurong,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/5-new-covid-19-cases-in-spore-including-4-linked-to-a-new-cluster-a-private-dinner|title=5 new Covid-19 cases in S'pore: 4 linked to new cluster involving Safra Jurong private dinner|last1=Choo|first1=Yun Ting|date=5 March 2020|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305215650/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/5-new-covid-19-cases-in-spore-including-4-linked-to-a-new-cluster-a-private-dinner|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> a boulder+ Gym shop at Aperia, Church of Singapore (Bukit Timah), [[Masjid Al-Muttaqin]], a [[PAP Community Foundation]] centre in Fengshan, [[Dover Court International School]],<ref name=\"SchClusters\">{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/new-covid-19-cases-pcf-sparkletots-fengshan-mar-25-12574708|titl