unning in 5 tries.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 16 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 25\u201340\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =New South Wales Team\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LIX| issue=18198\n| date = 1922-09-18\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220918.2.111\n| accessdate = 2019-08-29}}</ref>\n| away = New South Wales\n| try1 = [[Bert Avery]] 2, [[Ivan Littlewood]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] 2\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Maurice Wetherill]]\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 3\n| try2 = Toohey, Ives, Latta 2, Gray, [[Frank Burge]] 5\n| con2 = Horder 2, [[Frank Burge]] 3\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 20000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n\n===Auckland Province v New South Wales===\nA few days after the match with New South Wales an Auckland provincial team took on the touring side. The Auckland team was largely made up of Auckland club players but also included William Te Whata and a handful of others from the Waikato. They lost a tight match by 21 points to 20. [[Frank Burge]] was ordered off for disputing Wilson's try late in the match.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland Province\n| score = 20\u201321\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =League \"Rep\" Match/New South Wales Team/Game Against Province/Win by 21 Points to 20\n| page = 9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LIX| issue=18201\n| date = 1922-09-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220921.2.109\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = New South Wales\n| try1 = [[Bert Laing]] 2, [[Maurice Wetherill]], Billy Wilson\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = H Horder, W Toohey 2, B Grey, [[Frank Burge]]\n| con2 = H Horder, [[Frank Burge]] 2\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 1\n| attendance = 5500\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n\n===South Auckland v Auckland (Northern Union Challenge Cup)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| score = 26\u201318\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =South Auckland Win/Fast and Open League Play/Auckland Thirteen Defeated/28-16 At the Close\n| page = 6\n| work = Waikato Times| volume=96| issue=15056\n| date = 1922-10-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/WT19221002.2.66\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Hemmingway, [[Huatahi 'Brownie' Paki|Brownie Paki]], Bishop, Wilson, Jackson, Guthrie\n| con1 = Hemmingway 3, [[Wilson Hall (rugby league)|Wilson Hall]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]], [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], Nelson\n| con2 = [[Maurice Wetherill]], [[Clarrie Polson]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Steele Park, Hamilton\n| attendance = 2500\n| referee = A Harlock\n}}\n\n===Bay of Plenty v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Bay of Plenty\n| score = 26\u201333\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland League Team in Tauranga/Match Against Bay of Plenty\n| page = 3\n| work = Bay of Plenty Times| volume=LI| issue=8109\n| date = 1922-10-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/BOPT19221007.2.15\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Morrison, [[George Iles]], H Hume, G Gardiner, D Barclay, Ahomiro\n| con1 = G Gardiner 2, Ahomiro\n| pen1 = G Gardiner\n| try2 = [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] 3, J Johnson, [[Clarrie Polson]], F Wilson, [[Wally Somers]]\n| con2 = Mike Flynn, M Webb 2, [[Clarrie Polson]] 2\n| pen2 = M Webb\n| stadium = Tauranga\n| attendance =\n| referee = A Crane\n}}\n\n==Auckland Representative Matches Played and Scorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Name!!Club Team!!Play!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Mark!!Point